messages.text: Yes. Once I find Tasha I’ll signal you.
If he finds out you are here, he might try and hurt her.
Don’t hesitate to call us… We have backup.
Your daughter is waiting for you…
She misses you so much. It’s quite endearing…
Now that’s no way to respond to your husband.
Todd…Just tell me where you are.
And take the fun out of it?!
You have to come find us!!
It’ll be fun… I’ve set up a type of scavenger hunt…
I’m not playing this stupid game.
You know how much Tasha loves hide and seek :)
A freaking ax swung down as I opened the door! Really?!
I think it nicked my forehead…
There are certain…uh…surprises in store for you.
Do you want to see your daughter again or not?
I might not see her if I die first!
You okay? We heard a scream?
Should I call in the units?
No. Not yet. I’m not sure where he is.
Follow the arrows up the stairs...
I think they're works of art. Took me forever to make them.
Okay - I’m at the top of the stairs. God, it reeks.
The far door…where my studio used to be…
Red always has been my favorite color.
Do you really think I'd kill my own daughter? Our daughter?
I just want to be with her. That’s what this is all about.
Lives in the blue house across the street?
Don’t act like you don’t know him…
Ugh, this is where the stench is coming from.
But I saw how he looked at you.
I don’t know what you’re talking about?!
The way he smiled every time you passed his house!
He was just being a kind neighbor! That’s what neighbors do!!
And for that he gets his guts spread all over the place?!
His blood painted on the walls?!
Crossing the line if you ask me…
So, I figured I’d combine your two favorite things...
Wow. That's your response to a man who just wants to care for you?
This can end now…if you bring her out, and just disappear.
If you can do that, I will forget any of this ever happened.
But then we’ll be back in the same place from where we started...
I just want my daughter. I didn’t come here for you. I came here for Tasha.
I’m willing to help you escape if you just grant me that request.
I came here with the police.
Calm down. I’m the only one in the house at the moment.
And they don’t know where you are in here.
They are waiting for me to contact them to come in.
But I can help you get out of here...
IF you promise to give back my daughter and leave us alone.
No prison, no punishment, just flee...
Yes. Pull down the stairs and climb up.
Oh god! Thank you Todd! Thank you.
The entrance is above the studio.
Okay. Stay put. We are coming.
We’ll get the girl, don’t worry.
If you kill him, I don’t care.
There is nothing up here but old furniture and... a camera. Holy shit -
Tsk Tsk Carol… Why would you lie to me??
I knew from the beginning that you weren’t alone.
You just buried yourself deeper in lies.
I gave you a piece of her.
It’s your fault. You started this.
Now what do I do? I can’t trust you anymore…
But I will take something she does need if you do this again.
What do you want from me?!
I’ll give you one more chance.
Because I really do want to be with you and I love you.
I don't know what to say.
I will tell you where we are... For real this time.
But I’ll know if you come alone or not.
If not, I will not hesitate to take more of your daughter.
I PROMISE - I'll come alone. Just please don’t hurt her.
